title: Shaun White’s Winning Run – 2016 Burton US Open Halfpipe
description: Since his showing in the semifinals, Shaun White became a favorite to win his sixth Burton US Open Halfpipe Championship. With his signature massive airs and mesmerizing technical tricks, he fulfilled that destiny with this first run 95.62.

transcripts: His lifetime snowboard sponsor now watch this, this is going to be the biggest air you've seen all day! Are you kidding me! Shaun White going at least 25 feet out of the pipe on his first hip and following it up with back-to-back double corks. This is huge if he stays on his feet right now this score will be in the nineties and there's the double McTwist 1260 we didn't even see that in the semifinals were outside 720 tail grab and Shaun White just eat this half bite into submission.
